    "recap_headline": "University of Louisiana at Lafayette Athletics",
    "recap_text": "SAN MARCOS, Texas \u2013\nJaquae Stewart hit the first pitch he saw for a grand slam in the bottom of the eighth inning as Texas State defeated No. 25-ranked Louisiana, 4-1, in the opening game of a three-game Sun Belt Conference series on Friday before a crowd of 1,423 at Bobcat Ballpark.\nThe eighth inning produced the game's only runs as Kyle Froehlich and\nSawyer Pruitt\nwere locked in a classic pitcher's duel for seven innings.\nFroehlich allowed just two hits over the first seven innings for Texas State (13-8, 1-3 SBC) and retired 16 consecutive batters after\nMark Collins\nsingled with two outs in the second inning. Froehlich recorded nine of his 10 strikeouts during that stretch and departed after\nSteven Spalitta\ntripled to deep right-center field to lead off the eighth.\nBlaze Rodriguez\nthen lined a one-out single to left field off reliever Wade Cooper (1-0) to break the scoreless tie.\nMeanwhile, Louisiana starter\nSawyer Pruitt\nsparkled through a season-high seven innings of work, allowing three hits while walking two and striking out eight in a 99-pitch performance. Pruitt departed after allowing a hit and a walk with two outs in the seventh before getting Clayton Namken to hit into a force play. Pruitt did not allow a runner past second base during his outing.\nLouisiana (16-6, 2-2 SBC) turned to right-hander\nParker Smith\n(0-2) in the bottom of the eighth inning. Smith retired the first two hitters before Jackson Cotton singled, Manny Salas was hit by a pitch and Rashawn Galloway walked to load the bases.\nFreshman left-hander\nCole Flanagan\nrelieved, and Stewart hit the first-pitch fastball over the right-field wall for the game-winning grand slam.\nThe teams will meet in Game 2 of the series Saturday at 2:30 p.m. Louisiana is expected to send\nAndrew Herrmann\n(3-0, 2.88 ERA) to the mound in an attempt to even the series.\nFans are encouraged to stay engaged with the Ragin' Cajuns by downloading the #GeauxCajuns app. Click\nhere\nfor iOS/Apple platforms and\nhere\nfor Android platforms.\nFor the latest updates on Ragin' Cajuns baseball, follow on Facebook (RaginCajunsBaseball), Twitter (@RaginCajunsBSB) and Instagram (@RaginCajunsBSB) or check RaginCajuns.com.",
